''SD Valis''/''Syd of Valis'' received negative response from the gaming press.<ref name="BMDSMDsdv"/><ref name="FamSMDsdv"/> It received scores of 19.5 out of 30 and 3.9718 out of 10 in public polls taken by ''Mega Drive Fan'' and the Japanese ''[[Gemaga|Sega Saturn Magazine]]'' respectively.<ref name="MDFv4i5">{{cite magazine|url=https://retrocdn.net/index.php?title=File:Mdfan_JP_1992-05.pdf&page=115|title=Weekly Hit Chart|magazine={{ill|Mega Drive Fan|lt=Mega Drive Fan|ja|メガドライブFAN}}|issue=28|publisher=[[Tokuma Shoten]]|date=May 1992|page=115|lang=ja}}</ref><ref name="SSMjp9">{{cite magazine|url=https://retrocdn.net/index.php?title=File:SSM_JP_19950901_1995-09.pdf&page=87|script-title=ja:メガドラ読者レース|magazine=[[Gemaga|Sega Saturn Magazine]]|issue=9|publisher=[[SoftBank Creative]]|date=September 1995|page=85|lang=ja|access-date=2022-04-27|archive-date=2021-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314215823/https://retrocdn.net/index.php?title=File%3ASSM_JP_19950901_1995-09.pdf&page=87|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Games-X]]'' criticized its gameplay, short length and overall presentation.<ref name="GXsdv"/> ''Consoles +''{{'}} Navarro and Laurent Defrance commended the audio and manga-style character sprites but faulted their small size. They also criticized the game's imprecise scrolling, playability and length.<ref name="CPSMDsdv"/> ''Joypad''{{'}}s Olivier Prézeau gave positive remarks to its audiovisual presentation and controls,<ref name="JPSMDsov"/> however ''[[Joystick (magazine)|Joystick]]''{{'}}s Jean-Marc Demoly found it unpleasant to play, stating that "''Syd Of Valis'' is a game that I strongly advise against, unless somewhere deep inside you, a small dose of masochism is present."<ref name="JSSMDsov"/> ''[[MegaTech]]''{{'}}s Mark Patterson and Paul Glancey lambasted its presentation for the lack of options, simplistic sprites and low sound quality. Both Patterson and Glancey summarized that it was a "pretty poor attempt at producing a cute beat 'em up."<ref name="MegaTSMDsdv"/>

''[[Sega Force]]''{{'}}s Paul Mellerick bashed its "very dull" gameplay despite "great" levels and enemies, writing that "even platform addicts will only play it for a while".<ref name="SForceSMDsdv">{{cite magazine|last=Mellerick|first=Paul|url=https://archive.org/details/sega-force-04/page/n54/mode/1up|title=Advance Play! - Varis SD|magazine=[[Sega Force]]|issue=4|publisher=[[Europress Impact]]|date=April 1992|page=55}}</ref> ''[[Sega Pro]]''{{'}}s James Scullion gave ''SD Valis'' a mediocre outlook, recommending saving money for some other game.<ref name="SProSMDsdv"/> ''[[Console XS]]'' found it "mildly disturbing" due to the visual style.<ref name="CXSSMDsdv"/> ''Video Games''{{'}} Michael Paul faulted the controls for being slippery and imprecise, while gearing his criticism towards the graphical design, low-detailed sprite animations, audio and repetitive enemy patterns.<ref name="VGSSMDfsov"/> In contrast to most reviewers, ''[[GamePro]]''{{'}}s Feline Groovy gave high marks to the visuals, sound, controls and fun factor.<ref name="GameProSMDsov">{{cite magazine|last=Groovy|first=Feline|url=https://retrocdn.net/index.php?title=File:GamePro_US_037.pdf&page=42|title=Genesis ProReview: Syd of Valis|magazine=[[GamePro]]|issue=37|publisher=[[International Data Group|IDG]]|date=August 1992|page=40}}</ref> In a retrospective article from ''Hardcore Gaming 101'' dedicated to the [[Super deformed|SD]] remake, Kurt Kalata noted that the game's level design was improved over the original ''Valis II'' but equally dull.<ref name="SydofValisHG101">{{cite web|last=Kalata|first=Kurt|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/syd-of-valis/|title=Syd of Valis|work=[[Hardcore Gaming 101]]|date=July 9, 2012|access-date=2022-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718223330/http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/syd-of-valis/|archive-date=2018-07-18|url-status=live}}</ref>

